  "prompt": "Are there legal frameworks in place to combat money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several legal frameworks in place to combat money laundering at both national and international levels:\n\n1. International Frameworks:\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations Conventions\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n- Egmont Group of Financial Intelligence Units\n\n2. National Legislation:\n- Bank Secrecy Act (USA)\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) laws\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) regulations\n- Suspicious Transaction Reporting requirements\n\n3. Key Preventive Measures:\n- Customer due diligence\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Reporting suspicious activities\n- Asset freezing\n- International cooperation between law enforcement agencies\n\n4. Penalties:\n- Substantial financial fines\n- Criminal prosecution\n- Asset seizure\n- License revocation for financial institutions\n\n5. Specific Sectors Regulated:\n- Banks\n- Financial institutions\n- Cryptocurrency exchanges\n- Real estate\n- Gambling industries\n\nThese frameworks aim to detect, prevent, and prosecute money laundering activities by establishing comprehensive regulatory standards and enforcement mechanisms.\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any specific aspect of money laundering legal frameworks?",
